   domestic herbivores can be managed to minimize competition with wild
   herbivores and to enhance habitat by maximizing grassland structural
   heterogeneity (greater adaptive foraging options), creation of nutrient
   hotspots in the landscape and facilitation of high-quality grazing.
   Ecosystem service benefits to communities through controlled access to
   grazing resources in PAs, associated with appropriate disease
   management, can provide a conservation payment to promote communities'
   support of conservation of key wildlife migratory ranges and corridors
   outside PAs.}},
