   terraces. The higher spatial or temporal species turnover of plants and
   orthopterans in abandoned terraces and higher temporal plant nestedness
   in intensive than in traditional terraces were not due to increases in
   species pools within terraces. Because within-terrace environmental
   heterogeneity is thought to remain in abandoned and intensive terraces,
