Pages = {{84-92}},
Month = {{APR}},
Abstract = {{Vascular plant and bryophyte species richness, and bryophyte diaspore
   bank were studied in 14 Estonian coastal meadows that had been under two
   different grazing pressures for ca. 10 years. The aim of the study was
   to compare the effects of grazing intensity on the diversity of these
   plant groups, and on the bryophyte diaspore bank. The results showed
   that (1) intensive grazing increased bryophyte diversity, but not that
   of vascular plants or the diaspore bank; (2) vascular plant diversity
   was suppressed by litter cover; (3) vascular plant and bryophyte
   diversities were positively correlated; and (4) the species composition
   remained unaffected by grazing intensity.}},
